				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$42~\text{mm}\times40 \times 19~\text{mm}$\end{document} and weighs 52 grams. The digitizer assembly is approximately 56 mm in diameter and weighs approximately 50 gramsFig. 27
Location of the EDLCAM microphone on the Perseverance Rover. The microphone is located on the port side (Y-axis, rover coordinate frame) of the rover body, above the middle wheel

The three PUCs start to acquire image data immediately before parachute deployment at a frame rate of 75 fps (frames per second). After 30 seconds the frame rate drops to 30 fps until backshell separation, expected to occur approximately 98 seconds later. The total number of expected PUC images is ∼5,190\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
